HEADWORD: Gratinate
<hw>Grat"i*nate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>gratiner</ets>, v.i., to form a crust.]</ety> <fld>(Cookery)</fld>
<def>To cook, as macaroni, in a savory juice or sauce until the juice is
absorbed and a crisp surface forms.</def>⟦br⟧
